Pattern:
```cpp
// tensor.h
struct Tensor {
  float* data; // Raw pointer, does not own memory
  std::vector<int> shape;
  std::vector<int> strides;

  Tensor(float* data, std::vector<int> shape);
  float at(std::vector<int> indices);
};

// tensor.cpp
Tensor::Tensor(float* new_data, std::vector<int> new_shape) : data(new_data), shape(new_shape) {
  strides.push_back(1);
  for (int i = shape.size() - 1; i > 0; i--) {
    strides.push_back(strides.back() * shape[i]);
  }
  std::reverse(strides.begin(), strides.end());
}

float Tensor::at(std::vector<int> indices) {
  int offset = 0;
  for (int i = 0; i < indices.size(); i++) {
    offset += indices[i] * strides[i];
  }
  return data[offset];
}
```

**Stride Calculation Logic (Row-Major):**
1.  Initialize the stride for the last dimension to 1 (it's contiguous).
2.  Iterate backward through the dimensions (from `n-1` down to `1`).
3.  For each dimension `i`, its stride is `stride[i+1] * shape[i+1]` (i.e., the stride of the next dimension multiplied by the size of the next dimension).
4.  Reverse the resulting strides vector to match dimension order.
